	<meta content="Shirley Anne is a 60ft cruiser stern narrowboat fitted out to be a modern, light and airy boat. Key Features Boat Name Shirley Anne II Style Cruiser stern Length 60ft No. of Berths 2/4 Builder JL Pinder Year of Build 2015 Boat Safety Cert (BSS) 2020 Last Surveyed n/a Last Hull Backing 2015 (Two pack epoxy coated) Last Engine Service n/a Technical Specification Steelwork/Construction Boat builder: JL Pinder Fitted out by: Owner Construction: Steel Plating: 10/6/5/4 Length: 60ft Beam: 6ft 10in Air draft: n/a Water draft: 22in Engine &amp; Components Engine: Barrus Shire Engine Model: 45hp Engine Hours: 201 Cooling: Keel tanks Gearbox: PRM 150 Fuel capacity: 375 litres Bowthruster: Lewmar Electrics No. of alternators: 2 Size: 50amp &amp; 240amp Lighting: 12V Landline: Aft Inverter: n/a Batteries: n/a Generator: 3.5KW TravelPower Hot Water &amp; Heating Systems Source of hot water: Engine; c/heating &amp; immersion Other: n/a Calorifier: 60 litres Central heating: Webasto Solid fuel stove: n/a Water tank: Integral Capacity: 1100 litres &nbsp; Bathroom Engine make: Canaline 52 Type of toilet: Thetford C200 &amp; Aqua Marine toilet Bath/Shower: Shower Washbasin: Yes Galley (Kitchen) Cooking: Cooker 500 DIT Fridge: 12V Isotherm with icebox Gas System No. of bottles: 2 Location: Aft Supplying: Cooker only Fit Out Insulation: Sprayfoam Ballast: n/a Type of wood used: Ash Windows: 8 x 42”x 21” &amp; 2 x 24”x24” polished chrome with secondary glazing. Doors: steel stern doors &amp; 1/2glazed timber bow doors with stained glass. Side doors opposite dinette Inventory Fenders Windlasses Mooring pins Nav lights Ropes Floor Plan Layout Access The boat is accessed via centralised steel doors with sliding hatch from a cruiser stern rear deck. Bedroom 4ft fixed double bed, with two huge storage drawers under plus hanging &amp; shelving storage space to the foot of the bed. Useful small shelf for glasses, jewellery etc. when retiring for the night. Bathroom Corridor leads to an enclosed bathroom to the port side. Large shower unit with glass screen. The porcelain washbasin and waterproof wall boarding give this bathroom a modern feel. Two toilets in here, one cassette and the other a sea toilet and again plenty of that all important storage. Gallery Walk-through galley with a stunning sparkly cream granite worktop (the good stuff at 30mm thick). Plenty of cupboards for all that food, cutlery &amp; crockery. Full size cooker and 12v fridge. &nbsp; Dinette Raised L-shaped dinette and removable brown upholstery covers (new!), storage under and table which can altered to dining height or coffee table height if you prefer. Saloon Lovely, light and airy open plan saloon with freestanding armchairs which convert to berths. Counter height corner cupboard/ book case unit. This boat has plenty of 240V &amp; 12V sockets throughout with aerial points where you would expect. Other equipment Bowthruster Aft deck Pram cover &amp; forward deck slope cover The boat comes equipped with a limited complement of cruising equipment. Broker Summary Shirley Anne is a 60ft cruiser stern narrowboat fitted out to be a modern, light and airy boat. Built by JL Pinder and f fitted out by the owner to a very good standard. Lined in ash plywood with matching ash hardwood trims. Certainly achieved the modern look and feel he was aiming for with a touch of love. The boat has never been used and now lying at Evesham Marina. She would make an ideal liveaboard or for extended cruising. A great and affordable NEW build boat. Moorings also available. PLEASE CONTACT ME FOR FURTHER INFORMATION OR TO ARRANGE A VIEWING Disclaimer PLEASE NOTE: The information contained in this advertisement is based on our own inspection and information provided by the owner and is intended as a sales aid only to assist you to decide whether you would like to move to the next stage and view the boat yourself. Nothing contained herein constitutes a contract or offer. This is not a survey. We recommend that all boats are inspected by a qualified marine surveyor prior to purchase." name="description">
